Cell["\<\
\tArmed with the experience of our examples, let us now develop a \
mathematical model for probability, events, and sample spaces that proceeds \
from a minimal set of axioms to derive several of the most important basic \
properties of probability. A few other properties are given in the exercises. \
\>", "Text"],

